'''''Davis et al. v. The St. Louis Housing Authority''''' is a landmark class-action lawsuit filed in 1952 in [[St. Louis|Saint Louis, Missouri]] to challenge racial discrimination in public housing. The decision enjoined the Saint Louis Housing Authority from refusing to rent to qualified African Americans.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xp3jyLzSwuIC|title=African Americans in Downtown St. Louis|last=Sr|first=John A. Wright|date=2012-09-18|publisher=Arcadia Publishing|isbn=9781439614655|language=en}}</ref>

